title: Love Among the Chickens
creator: P. G. Wodehouse
description: Librivox recording of Love Among the Chickens by P. G. Wodehouse. Read by Mark Nelson Jeremy Garnet, a second-rate novelist, gets talked into joining his old pal Stanley Featheringstonehaugh Ukridge in an insane plan to start a chicken ranch. Garnet should bail out on his crazy friend, but he falls in love with one of Ukridge's neighbors, Phyllis. Soon he is up to his neck in sick chickens, bad debts, a hostile future father-in-law, a sinister plot, and dirty golf. It all gets a bit thick, what? (Summary by Mark Nelson) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. reviews.reviewbody:
I liked this story.  It had some humorous elements, lots of misadventures, and a happy ending.  What more could you want in a story?  

Summary above gives the general gist of the story.  Reader is excellent, as always.  

Enjoy!
